latestIgtvVideos.title: Her story
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Posted @withregram • @herstorytimes Presenting a Sneak Peek into the Journey of CAPT LAXMI SHAILESH JOSHI, AIR INDIA born with the Fascination of Flying- @pilotlaxmi 
#CaptainLaxmi  #CaptLaxmiJoshi #HERstoryTimes
“The machine will not know whether a man is flying it or a woman is flying it.” This is what Capt Laxmi Shailesh Joshi, Air India Boeing 777 Pilot. 
___________

Hailing her roots from Mumbai, she completed her schooling from North Bombay Welfare Society High School, Mumbai. At a very young age of 15, she had already garnered her love for being a pilot. As she grew up, she mastered her art and emerged victorious in her first flight operation in New Zealand. 

“Traditionally, women entering male-dominated professions in India encounter a wide array of obstacles. Therefore, many females in the airline industry have and continue to face hurdles simply because of their gender. However, I never thought twice about being in the airline industry. I never considered being a pilot different from being an engineer or a teacher. My father always stood as a constant who incessantly supported me through thick and thin. I was always taught that there are no limits for what I can do,” added Laxmi who has currently done 3000 odd hours of flight. 

Laxmi attributes her success of being an admired and reliable pilot to one thing, i.e. hard work. She has accomplished every extraordinary milestone she’s set out to do. “Anything you set your mind to do, just do it. Tomorrow it will be something else,” quoted Laxmi who has successfully carried out rescue operations in Paris

Attention all pilots! 

Hi everyone, I would like to introduce you to something exciting I have been working on for a while. As we all know times have been tough due to COVID-19 pandemic and it has had an impact on everyone including the aviation community. So, a new platform has launch called @airside from #CAE. It’s a platform made by pilots for pilots and I too have contributed. Stay tuned for my content piece that will be released soon! Create an account today to use the resume builder and be up to date with the latest information and interact with pilots all around the world. Plus you can view articles, listen to podcasts and do a whole lot more on their website www.aeroside.aero

This Women’s Day, Cosmopolitan India puts the spotlight on five women who don’t just ‘want it all’ but have ‘got it all’. Are they pretty? Indeed. But what makes them a class apart is that they are unstoppable, and they show other women what it’s like to be groundbreaking, sensational, inspirational, fearless…and ICONIC.

In a world riddled with uncertainty, commercial airline pilot and Covid-19 frontline worker, Laxmi Shailesh Joshi (@pilotlaxmi); actor, philanthropist and Padma Shri awardee, Raveena Tandon (@officialraveenatandon); digital content creator and former RJ, Karishma Gangwal (@rjkarishma); fashion and beauty content creator, Aastha Shah (@aasthashah97); Indian badminton player and two-time Olympic medallist, PV Sindhu (@pvsindhu1) are forces in their own right—women who defy all odds.
Want to take a cue and (also) make a difference? Well, no better time than now to celebrate that one trait, which makes you stand out.

Choose yourself and opt to be #MoreThanPretty with @mango @mangostores_india

Commercial airline pilot and Covid-19 frontline worker, Laxmi Shailesh Joshi (@pilotlaxmi) is #PrettyFearless because in the face of adversity, she chose her country before anything else. Speaking about being brave, Laxmi says: “When the pandemic hit the world, everyone was asked to stay at home. I, with many other pilots, chose to be a part of the Vande Bharat Mission, a great initiative taken by Air India airlines to help the cause. We were flying non-stop for this mission [to repatriate Indian nationals across the globe and bring in essential supplies to the country].”
Laxmi is #MoreThanPretty. She chased her dreams, bucked the odds, pushed her limits. So what’s stopping you? @mango @mangostores_india
